7. How can you handle errors in Power Automate flows?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ”¹ I usaually Common Error Handling Techniques:

1. Configure Run After:
â¤ Lets you specify when an action should run â€” e.g., only if the previous action fails or is skipped.
ğŸ“Œ Used to send alerts or log errors when something goes wrong.

2. Scope with Run Status Check:
â¤ Group actions inside a Scope, then use another Scope to handle success or failure.
ğŸ“Œ Helps in building try-catch-finally style logic.

3. Terminate Action:
â¤ Used to end a flow early with a custom status (Success, Failed, Cancelled).

4. Failure Notifications:
â¤ Add an action (like Send an email) in the error branch to notify admins or users.
